## Session 4: API Design (REST & gRPC Endpoints)

### Public REST API

```python
# === Video APIs ===

# Upload - Initiate resumable upload
# POST /api/v1/videos
# Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>
# Body: { "title": "My Video", "description": "...", "tags": ["tech"] }
# Response: { "video_id": "abc123", "upload_url": "https://upload.youtube.com/..." }

# Get video metadata
# GET /api/v1/videos/{video_id}
# Response: { "video_id": "abc123", "title": "...", "views": 1234567,
#             "stream_urls": { "240p": "...", "720p": "...", "1080p": "..." } }

# Update video
# PATCH /api/v1/videos/{video_id}
# Body: { "title": "Updated Title", "description": "..." }

# Delete video
# DELETE /api/v1/videos/{video_id}

# === Feed APIs ===

# Home feed (personalized)
# GET /api/v1/feed?page_token=xxx&page_size=20

# Channel videos
# GET /api/v1/channels/{channel_id}/videos?order=date&page_size=20

# Search
# GET /api/v1/search?q=python+tutorial&type=video&page_size=20

# === Interaction APIs ===

# Like/dislike
# POST /api/v1/videos/{video_id}/rate
# Body: { "rating": "like" }

# Comment
# POST /api/v1/videos/{video_id}/comments
# Body: { "text": "Great video!", "parent_id": null }

# Subscribe
# POST /api/v1/channels/{channel_id}/subscribe
```

### Resumable Upload Protocol

Large video files need resumable uploads -- a failed 200GB upload should not restart from zero:

```python
class ResumableUploadService:
    CHUNK_SIZE = 16 * 1024 * 1024  # 16MB chunks

    def initiate(self, video_id: str, file_size: int) -> str:
        session_id = str(uuid.uuid4())
        self.redis.hset(f"upload:{session_id}", mapping={
            "video_id": video_id,
            "file_size": file_size,
            "bytes_received": 0,
            "status": "active"
        })
        return session_id

    def upload_chunk(self, session_id: str, chunk: bytes,
                     offset: int) -> dict:
        session = self.redis.hgetall(f"upload:{session_id}")
        expected_offset = int(session["bytes_received"])

        if offset != expected_offset:
            return {"status": "error",
                    "expected_offset": expected_offset}

        # Append chunk to object store
        self.storage.append(
            bucket="raw-videos",
            key=f'{session["video_id"]}/original',
            data=chunk,
            offset=offset
        )

        new_offset = offset + len(chunk)
        self.redis.hset(f"upload:{session_id}",
                       "bytes_received", new_offset)

        if new_offset >= int(session["file_size"]):
            self._finalize_upload(session_id, session["video_id"])
            return {"status": "complete"}

        return {"status": "ok", "bytes_received": new_offset}
```

### Internal gRPC APIs

For service-to-service communication, YouTube uses **gRPC** (lower latency, binary protocol, streaming support):

```java
// Java client for gRPC transcoding service
// Proto definition:
// service TranscodingService {
//     rpc SubmitJob(TranscodeRequest) returns (TranscodeResponse);
//     rpc GetJobStatus(JobStatusRequest) returns (stream JobProgress);
// }

public class TranscodingClient {
    private final TranscodingServiceGrpc.TranscodingServiceStub stub;

    public void submitTranscodeJob(String videoId, String sourcePath) {
        TranscodeRequest request = TranscodeRequest.newBuilder()
            .setVideoId(videoId)
            .setSourcePath(sourcePath)
            .addTargetResolutions(Resolution.newBuilder()
                .setWidth(1920).setHeight(1080).setBitrateKbps(6000))
            .addTargetResolutions(Resolution.newBuilder()
                .setWidth(1280).setHeight(720).setBitrateKbps(3000))
            .addTargetResolutions(Resolution.newBuilder()
                .setWidth(640).setHeight(360).setBitrateKbps(700))
            .setCodec("h264")
            .build();

        stub.submitJob(request, new StreamObserver<TranscodeResponse>() {
            @Override
            public void onNext(TranscodeResponse response) {
                log.info("Job submitted: {}", response.getJobId());
            }
            @Override
            public void onError(Throwable t) { log.error("Submit failed", t); }
            @Override
            public void onCompleted() {}
        });
    }
}
```

