### Location Service Scaling

The Location Service handles the highest QPS (1.25M updates/sec globally). Here is how it scales:

```java
// Java: Partitioned location service
public class LocationServiceCluster {
    private static final int NUM_PARTITIONS = 1024;

    /**
     * Partition drivers by geographic region to ensure
     * drivers in the same area are on the same partition.
     */
    public int getPartition(double lat, double lng) {
        // Use H3 index at resolution 4 (~1,770 sq km hexagons)
        long h3Index = H3.geoToH3(lat, lng, 4);
        return (int)(h3Index % NUM_PARTITIONS);
    }

    /**
     * Each partition handles location updates and proximity queries
     * for its geographic region.
     */
    public void handleLocationUpdate(String driverId,
                                      double lat, double lng) {
        int partition = getPartition(lat, lng);
        LocationPartition p = getPartition(partition);

        // Update in-memory spatial index
        p.updateDriver(driverId, lat, lng);

        // Write to Redis for persistence
        p.getRedis().geoadd("drivers:" + partition, lng, lat, driverId);

        // Publish to Kafka for analytics
        kafkaProducer.send("driver-locations",
            String.valueOf(partition),
            new LocationUpdate(driverId, lat, lng, Instant.now()));
    }
}
