### Handling Gateway Failures

When a Gateway server crashes, all its connections drop. Clients must reconnect:

```java
// Java - Client reconnection with exponential backoff
public class ReconnectionManager {
    private static final int MAX_RETRIES = 10;
    private static final long BASE_DELAY_MS = 1000;

    public void reconnect() {
        int attempt = 0;
        while (attempt < MAX_RETRIES) {
            try {
                WebSocket ws = connectToGateway();
                syncOfflineMessages(ws);
                return;
            } catch (ConnectionException e) {
                long delay = Math.min(
                    BASE_DELAY_MS * (1L << attempt),
                    30_000
                ) + ThreadLocalRandom.current().nextLong(1000);
                Thread.sleep(delay);
                attempt++;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

