## Session 8: Reliability & Message Delivery Guarantees

### Delivery Guarantee Levels

| Guarantee | Meaning | WhatsApp? |
|-----------|---------|-----------|
| At-most-once | Fire and forget | No |
| **At-least-once** | Retry until ACKed | **Yes** |
| Exactly-once | Deduplicate at receiver | Via idempotency keys |

WhatsApp provides **at-least-once delivery** with **client-side deduplication** to achieve effective exactly-once semantics.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Sender
    participant S as Server
    participant B as Receiver

    A->>S: Message (id=abc123)
    S-->>A: ACK (stored)
    S->>B: Deliver message
    Note over S,B: No ACK received (B crashed?)
    S->>B: Retry deliver message
    B->>S: ACK (delivered)
    Note over B: Dedup: seen abc123 before? skip
    S->>A: Status: DELIVERED
```

### Retry with Idempotency

```python
class ReliableDelivery:
    MAX_RETRIES = 5
    RETRY_DELAYS = [1, 2, 5, 15, 30]  # seconds

    async def deliver_with_retry(self, recipient_id: str, message):
        for attempt in range(self.MAX_RETRIES):
            try:
                conn = self.registry.lookup(recipient_id)
                if conn:
                    ack = await self.gateway.deliver(conn, message, timeout=5)
                    if ack:
                        self.message_store.mark_delivered(message.id, recipient_id)
                        return True
                else:
                    # User offline -- queue it
                    self.offline_queue.enqueue(recipient_id, message)
                    return True
            except TimeoutError:
                delay = self.RETRY_DELAYS[attempt]
                await asyncio.sleep(delay)

        # All retries failed -- store in offline queue as fallback
        self.offline_queue.enqueue(recipient_id, message)
        return False
```

### Client-Side Deduplication

```java
// Java - Receiver-side deduplication
public class MessageDeduplicator {
    private final BloomFilter<String> bloomFilter;
    private final LinkedHashSet<String> recentIds;
    private static final int MAX_RECENT = 100_000;

    public boolean isDuplicate(String messageId) {
        // Fast path: bloom filter says definitely not seen
        if (!bloomFilter.mightContain(messageId)) {
            bloomFilter.put(messageId);
            addToRecent(messageId);
            return false;
        }
        // Bloom filter says maybe seen -- check exact set
        return recentIds.contains(messageId);
    }

    private void addToRecent(String messageId) {
        if (recentIds.size() >= MAX_RECENT) {
            String oldest = recentIds.iterator().next();
            recentIds.remove(oldest);
        }
        recentIds.add(messageId);
    }
}
```

