### Failure Scenarios and Handling

| Failure | Impact | Mitigation |
|---------|--------|------------|
| Gateway crash | Connections drop | Client reconnects; offline queue catches messages |
| Chat Service crash | Messages not routed | Kafka buffers; consumer restart picks up |
| Database unavailable | Messages not persisted | Write to Kafka first (WAL); replay later |
| Redis (registry) crash | Cannot route messages | Redis Cluster with replicas; fallback to broadcast |
| Network partition | Region isolated | Multi-region queues; converge after healing |

### Write-Ahead Log Pattern

```java
// Java - WAL for message durability
public class MessagePipeline {
    private final KafkaProducer<String, Message> kafka;
    private final MessageStore database;

    public CompletableFuture<Void> processMessage(Message msg) {
        // Step 1: Write to Kafka FIRST (durable log)
        return kafka.send("messages", msg.getConversationId(), msg)
            .thenCompose(record -> {
                // Step 2: Then write to database
                return database.save(msg);
            })
            .thenCompose(saved -> {
                // Step 3: Then deliver to recipient
                return deliveryService.deliver(msg);
            });
    }
}
```

