### Fan-out Lag Monitoring

The most critical metric for Twitter is **fan-out lag** — the time between a tweet being posted and it appearing in all followers' timelines.

```python
class FanOutLagMonitor:
    def measure_lag(self, tweet_id: int):
        """Measure end-to-end fan-out latency."""
        tweet = self.tweet_store.get(tweet_id)
        created_at = tweet.created_at

        # Sample 100 random followers
        followers = self.social_graph.get_random_followers(tweet.user_id, 100)

        lags = []
        for follower_id in followers:
            timeline = self.redis.zscore(f"timeline:{follower_id}", str(tweet_id))
            if timeline:
                lag = timeline - created_at
                lags.append(lag)

        p50 = sorted(lags)[len(lags) // 2] if lags else None
        p99 = sorted(lags)[int(len(lags) * 0.99)] if lags else None

        self.metrics.gauge("fanout.lag.p50", p50)
        self.metrics.gauge("fanout.lag.p99", p99)

        if p99 and p99 > 30:
            self.alert("Fan-out lag p99 exceeds 30s", severity="HIGH")
