### User Activity Store (Cassandra)

Play history is write-heavy (millions of play events per second) and queried by user + time range. Cassandra is ideal.

```sql
-- CQL (Cassandra Query Language)
CREATE TABLE play_history (
    user_id     UUID,
    played_at   TIMESTAMP,
    track_id    UUID,
    duration_ms INT,
    context     TEXT,     -- 'playlist', 'album', 'radio', 'search'
    context_id  UUID,
    skipped     BOOLEAN,
    PRIMARY KEY (user_id, played_at)
) WITH CLUSTERING ORDER BY (played_at DESC)
  AND default_time_to_live = 31536000;  -- 1 year TTL
```

Partition key = user_id means all plays for one user live on the same partition. Clustering key = played_at DESC means most recent plays come first.

