### Audio Streaming Protocol

Spotify uses **HTTP Range requests** for audio streaming -- not WebSockets or custom protocols.

```
Client                          CDN Edge
  |-- GET /audio/track123.ogg ------>|
  |   Range: bytes=0-65535           |
  |<-------- 206 Partial Content ----|
  |   Content-Range: bytes 0-65535/3500000
  |                                  |
  |-- GET /audio/track123.ogg ------>|  (next chunk)
  |   Range: bytes=65536-131071      |
  |<-------- 206 Partial Content ----|
```

This approach allows **seeking** (jump to any position), **quality switching** mid-stream, and **resume after network drops**.

### Interview Tip

> Emphasize the use of **signed URLs** for streaming. The API server generates a time-limited, user-specific CDN URL. This prevents unauthorized sharing of direct audio links. The signature includes user_id, expiry, and an HMAC -- the CDN validates this before serving audio.

