### CDN Tiered Caching Strategy

The key insight: **the top 1% of tracks serve ~80% of all streams.** This extreme skew makes CDN caching incredibly effective.

| Tier | Location | Content | Hit Rate | Latency |
|------|----------|---------|----------|---------|
| **Edge POP** | 200+ cities worldwide | Top 1% tracks (~1M songs) | ~80% | <10ms |
| **Regional Hub** | 20-30 regions | Top 20% tracks (~20M songs) | ~95% cumulative | <50ms |
| **Origin** | 3-5 data centers | Full catalog (100M tracks) | 100% | 100-300ms |

```python
class CDNRoutingService:
    POPULARITY_TIERS = {
        "hot": 0.01,     # top 1% -> edge cache
        "warm": 0.20,    # top 20% -> regional cache
        "cold": 1.0,     # rest -> origin
    }

    def get_stream_url(self, track_id, user_region):
        track = self.catalog.get(track_id)
        popularity_rank = track.popularity_percentile

        if popularity_rank <= 0.01:
            edge_pop = self.get_nearest_edge(user_region)
            return f"https://{edge_pop}.cdn.spotify.com/audio/{track_id}"
        elif popularity_rank <= 0.20:
            regional = self.get_regional_hub(user_region)
            return f"https://{regional}.cdn.spotify.com/audio/{track_id}"
        else:
            return f"https://origin.cdn.spotify.com/audio/{track_id}"

    def preload_edge_cache(self, edge_pop):
        hot_tracks = self.catalog.get_top_tracks(percentile=0.01)
        for track in hot_tracks:
            for quality in ["96", "160", "320"]:
                self.cdn.prefetch(edge_pop, track.storage_key(quality))
