### The Payment Flow: Authorize, Capture, Settle

Understanding the payment lifecycle is critical:

```
1. AUTHORIZE: "Can this card pay $100?" -> Card network -> Issuing bank -> Yes/No
2. CAPTURE:   "Take the $100" -> Holds become actual charges
3. SETTLE:    "Transfer $97 to merchant" (after Stripe 2.9% + $0.30 fee)
4. PAYOUT:    "Send accumulated balance to merchant bank account"
```

### Service Decomposition

| Service | Responsibility | Criticality |
|---------|---------------|-------------|
| **Payment Service** | Orchestrates the payment state machine | Critical -- must never lose a payment |
| **Tokenization Service** | Converts card numbers to tokens (PCI zone) | Critical -- handles sensitive data |
| **Fraud Detection** | Real-time risk scoring (Radar) | High -- runs on every transaction |
| **Ledger Service** | Double-entry bookkeeping | Critical -- financial source of truth |
| **Webhook Service** | Async event delivery to merchants | High -- merchants depend on events |
| **Subscription Service** | Recurring billing, dunning | Medium -- batch-oriented |
| **Gateway Adapter** | Abstraction over card networks | Critical -- external integration |
| **Settlement Service** | Daily batch settlement with banks | Critical -- handles actual money movement |

