### Data Sovereignty and Regional Deployment

Payment data has strict regulatory requirements by region:

| Region | Regulation | Requirement |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| **EU** | GDPR + PSD2 | EU cardholder data must stay in EU data centers |
| **US** | PCI DSS | Cardholder data encrypted, network segmented |
| **India** | RBI guidelines | Payment data must be stored in India |
| **Australia** | CDR | Consumer data rights, data residency |

```python
class PaymentRouter:
    REGION_MAP = {
        "US": "us-east-1",
        "CA": "us-east-1",
        "GB": "eu-west-1",
        "DE": "eu-west-1",
        "FR": "eu-west-1",
        "IN": "ap-south-1",
        "AU": "ap-southeast-2",
        "JP": "ap-northeast-1",
    }

    def route(self, charge_request):
        # 1. Route by card issuing country (BIN lookup)
        card_country = self.bin_lookup.get_country(charge_request.card_bin)
        if card_country in self.REGION_MAP:
            return self.REGION_MAP[card_country]

        # 2. Fallback to merchant registered country
        merchant = self.merchant_service.get(charge_request.merchant_id)
        if merchant.country in self.REGION_MAP:
            return self.REGION_MAP[merchant.country]

        # 3. Default to US
        return "us-east-1"

    def route_to_card_network(self, charge_request):
        card_brand = charge_request.card_brand
        card_country = self.bin_lookup.get_country(charge_request.card_bin)

        network_endpoints = {
            ("visa", "US"): "https://visa-us.gateway.stripe.com",
            ("visa", "EU"): "https://visa-eu.gateway.stripe.com",
            ("mastercard", "US"): "https://mc-us.gateway.stripe.com",
            ("mastercard", "EU"): "https://mc-eu.gateway.stripe.com",
        }
        region = "EU" if card_country in EU_COUNTRIES else "US"
        return network_endpoints.get((card_brand, region), self.default_endpoint)
